# @COMMENT: This fragment comes from MZTXV25P423C, in the biography of Muḥammad b. Ṭalḥah b. Yazīd b. Rukānah ʿAbd Yazīd al-Muṭṭalibī al-Qurashī, and seeks to establish the relationship between him and Ibn Isḥāq. Muḥammad b. Ṭalḥah b. Yazīd is cited twice by WZATB in HSNXV01P565C and in HSNXV02P520B. He is cited several times in WSACD. Also see WAIYA, WYBWS, WYWAT, WSFAB, WAANH, WABAH, WMMRA, WAKMW, WZMHR, WSYSL, WISUL, WAMRR, WARBS, WJHZA, WMSAH, WARMZ, WISIB, WAWAA, WBSAB, and WYAHA. BNTHV07P377D states that he died in Madīnah at the beginning of Hishām b. ʿAbd al-Mālik's reign (r. 105/724 to 125/743). Placement based on location of earliest reference to Muḥammad b. Ṭalḥah in WSACD. @EC_03/22/23@

