VAR_KTHSV01P364A وروى البلوي عن @TR2_CUZD@ عمارة بن زيد عن @TR1_SACD@ إبراهيم بن سعد عن محمد بن اسحاق حدثني يحيى بن عبد الله بن الحارث عن أبيه عن ابن عباس قصة قتال علي الجن بالبئر ذات العلم التي بالجحفة حين بعثه رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم يستقي لهم الماء فأرادوا منعه وقطعوا الدلو فنزل إليهم وهي قصة مطولة منكرة جدا والله أعلم. @KTHBV02P344A_END_WSACD

# @TBTCV01P357A_BEG_WSACD حدثنا عبيد الله بن سعد قال حدثنا @TR2_YISI@ عمي قال حدثنا @TR1_SACD@ أبي عن ابن إسحاق عن سلمة بن كهيل أنه قرأها في مصحف أبي بن كعب مع @QURS113A001_BEG قل أعوذ برب الفلق @QURS113A001_END و @QURS114A001_BEG قل أعوذ برب الناس @QURS114A001_END مكتوبة. @TBTCV01P357A_END_WSACD
PageV01P357
# @COMMENT: Passage not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. Refers a version of the Qurʾān copied by Ubayy b. Kaʿb that contained two Qurʾānic passages, Qurʾān 113:001 and Qurʾān 114:001. Passage also found in WMHNS but that states that Ibn Isḥāq read the muṣḥaf Ubayy b. Kaʿb and goes on to quote a portion of the text. Ubayy b. Kaʿb is mentioned twice by WZATB in the redaction of Ibn Hishām: as a participant at Badr (HSNXV01P703C) and as receiving two shares from the dispribution of lots following Khaybar (HSNXV02P358A). Ibn Isḥāq quotes traditions from Ubayy b. Kaʿb extensively in WSFAB on different sections of the Qurʾān, as does WSACD. According to Muḥammad b. Saʿd, Ubayy was was among the first people of Yabrib to give allegiance to Muḥammad at ʿAqabah and was unusual in that he was literate. He made copies of sections of the Qurʾān in Muḥammad’s lifetime and was one of the most important memorizers of the text. He was one of the people ʿUthmān turned to in producing the so-called ʿUthmānī Codex. WMSAH also includes a similar passage without mentioning Ubayy b. Kaʿb. The WMSAH reference to the sūrah is set in the voice of ʿAqabah b. ʿĀmir, who says that he was traveling with Muḥammad when, between Juḥfah and al-Abwāʾ (on the route between Mecca and Madīnah), it suddenly became dark and the wind began to blow. Muḥammad then turns to ʿAqabah and says to recite the sūrah. WHWXV04P572A places the context of the sūrah in the story of Labīd b. Aʿṣam, a member of the Jewish Zurayq tribe, who is said to have cast a spell on Muḥammad by tying eleven knots in a rope and casting it in the well of Dharwān. This story is alluded to in WZATB on HSNXV01P515D but the sūrah is not mentioned, nor is the name of the well. Labīd b. Aʿṣam appears to be mentioned only in WZATB and does not occur elsewhere in the witnessed corpus. AMQMV01P198B quotes Ibn Isḥāq and "others," but does not cite a witness, recounting the story of Labīd b. Aʿṣam, the curse, and the well of Dharwān, although he states that some say the well was known as "Dhū Arwān" (this is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām). Dhū Arwān is not found in the witnessed corpus and is not mentioned except in AMQMV01P198B. From the context of the passage it is not possible to know where this should be placed. Given the reference to Juḥfah and al-Abwāʾ in WMSAH placement is provisional after the story of the approach toward Mecca on the day of Ḥudaybīyah and the role Juḥfah plays in it. @EC_01/17/23@

