VAR_ZTKXV01P569E قال ابن إسحاق ثم كانت حنين فلما فرغ رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم من حنين سار إلى الطائف حدثنا @TR2_AMIB@ أحمد بن محمد قال حدثنا @TR1_SACD@ إبراهيم عن ابن إسحاق عن بعض أصحابه عن ابن مكدم قال فحاصرهم بضعا وعشرين ليلة وفي ذلك الحصار نزل أبو بكرة إلى رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم قال ابن إسحاق أبو بكرة اسمه مسروح كذا قال. @ZTTHV02P022C_END_WSACD
PageV02P022
# @COMMENT: This is a compound passage that provides an isnād for the second half of the entry. The first part refers to the Battle of Ḥunayn and the following Battle for Ṭāʾif. A similar passage is found in WZATB on HSNXV02P478E that is placed at the beginning of the story of Ṭāʾif, although the passage is longer and more detailed than the fragment found in WSACD. Just prior to that is a breif mention of the Thaqīf on HSNXV02P478C, which, given the passage that follows, seems like a logical place to insert the passage. ZTTHV02P023A, below, contains similar elements but is worded differently and contains more detail. Note that both are related by AMIB. A similar passage, worded differently, is also found in WJHZA. No other version of the fragment is found in the corpus. @EC_02/02/23@ The second part refers to the actual Battle for Ṭāʾif. A similar passage is found in WZATB on HSNXV02P482C, although Abū̄ Bakrah, or his ism Masrūḥ, are not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. He was Nufayʿ b. al-Ḥārith b. Kaladah b. ʿAmr al-Thaqafī. Some say his name was Masrūḥ. He was one of four slaves who came out from Ṭāʾif whom the prophet freed. He was a companion and a source of some traditions. He died in the year 52/672 (HJTTV10P469A-470A). Abū̄ Bakrah is mentioned in WSFAB is a passage treating the same topic but constructed completely differently. He is also mentioned in WYBWS and WJHZA also in reference to Ṭāʾif. The name clairification is also found in WYBWS, WMUAL, and WMSAH. @EC_02/03/23@

# @ZTKXV01P569E_BEG_WSACD
VAR_ZTKXV01P569E حدثنا @TR2_AMIB@ أحمد بن محمد بن أيوب قال حدثنا @TR1_SACD@ إبراهيم بن سعد عن ابن إسحاق قال أبو بكرة واسمه مسروح وكان للحارث بن كلدة. @ZTKXV01P569E_END_WSACD
