# @COMMENT: This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. Placement based on content. The description of the events surrounding Muḥammad's death depicted in TDSHV17P054A appears to be the only instance in which Ibn Isḥāq is cited along with a witness. See THRXV06P098A and HJRSV07P111A for an analogous passage attributed to Ibn Isḥāq without a witness. RWDXV07P593A, BRSXV04P1650A, SMHHV02P064A contanin analogous passages but do not provide a source or an isnād. For analogous passages but attributed to the isnād: Ṣaʿṣaʿam al-Hudhaylī to his son al-Ḥaramās b. Ṣaʿṣaʿah al-Hudhaylī, see JWRXV01P231A.

