# @COMMENT: [] indicates the redaction of material between the tradition that the chain of transmission. 

# @DLKXV03P1167A_BEG_WSACD
VAR_DLKXV03P1167A VAR_THSMV01P034A VAR_MQRXV01P171A حدثنا علي بن معبد قال حدثنا @TR2_YISI@ أبو يوسف يعقوب بن إبراهيم بن سعد بن إبراهيم بن عبد الله بن عوف قال حدثني @TR1_SACD@ أبي عن ابن إسحاق قال حدثني نافع مولى عبد الله بن عمر أن عبد الله بن عمر كان يقول الأذنان من الرأس فامسحوا بهما. @DLKXV03P1167A_END_WSACD
PageV03P1167
# @COMMENT: This fragment, focusing on wiping over the ears for ablution, is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. This passage is also found in WSACD and WMYKA. A longer version of this fragment in found in WASKA that contains a different isnād (ʿAbd Allāh b. ʿAbbās to ʿUbayd Allāh al-Khawlānī to Muḥammad b. Ṭalḥah b. Yazīd to Ibn Isḥāq) and places the recollection in the context of an event, witnessed by ʿAbd Allāh b. ʿAbbās, when ʿAlī b. Abī Ṭālib spilled water he had planned to use for ablutions. He then recalls how both ʿAlī and Ibn ʿAbbās had witnesses Muḥammad perform wudūʿ and the disagreements about wudūʿ that occurred after Muḥammad’s death. There is not date given and ʿAlī is not referred to as the Caliph, so it must have occurred between Muḥammad’s death in 662 and ʿAlī’s assumption of the Caliphate in 656. Lacking other information, placement will be in fiqh section under ablutions. @EC_03/01/23@

# @THSMV01P034A_BEG_WSACD
