### ||||| أغتسل 

# @TBJXV08P180A_BEG_WSACD دثنا ابن حميد قال ثنا @TR1_YWAT@ أبو تميلة ح وحدثني @TR2_YISI@ يعقوب بن إبراهيم قال ثنا PageV08P180 @TR1_ISUL@ ابن علية قالا جميعا ثنا محمد بن إسحاق قال ثني محمد بن طلحة بن يزيد بن ركانة عن عبيد الله الخولاني عن ابن عباس قال قال علي بن أبي طالب ألا أتوضأ لكم وضوء رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم قال قلنا نعم فتوضأ فلما غسل وجهه ألقم إبهاميه ما أقبل من أذنيه قال ثم لما مسح برأسه مسح أذنيه من ظهورهما. @TBJXV08P180A_END_WSACD
PageV08P181
# @COMMENT: This fragment is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. There are a complex of three traditions that revolve around ʿAlī b. Abī Ṭālib and his performance of wuḍūʿ. Although they most likely deal with the same event since ʿAbd Allāh b. ʿAbbās is the witness for each, they are sufficiently different to treat as distinct traditions. The fragment referred to here is the “demonstration” tradition, where ʿAlī demonstrates how the prophet did wuḍūʿ, and it is characterized by references to ʿAlī “wiping” (مسح) himself without a stated context. This tradition is found in WYWAT, WSACD, and WISUL. The second tradition is referred to here as the "entering" tradition, where ʿAlī enters the home of ʿAbd Allāh b. ʿAbbās and asks for water for wuḍūʿ. This tradition is found in WYWAT, WASKA, WMSAH, WISUL, and WISIB, WARMZ. The final tradition in the complex is the "witness" tradition in which ʿAlī describes seeing the prophet do wuḍūʿ. This tradition is found in WYWAT. @EC_03/09/23@

