# @BKHTV01P522A_BEG_WSACD
VAR_BKHBV01P213A VAR_TDSHV55P111C حدثني عبيد الله بن سعد قال PageV01P522 حدثنا @TR2_YISI@ عمي قال حدثنا @TR1_SACD@ أبي عن ابن إسحاق قال حدثني محمد بن قيس مولى يعقوب القبطي وكان قاصا قال قصصت على عمر بن عبد العزيز وهو أمير المدينة فقال عمر بن عبد العزيز حدثنا أبو سلمة عن أبي هريرة عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم أنه سجد في @QURS84A001_BEG إذا السماء انشقت @QURS84A001_END
@BKHTV01P522A_END_WSACD
PageV01P522
# @COMMENT: This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām and appears to be the only witness to the story in the Ibn Isḥāq corpus. The passage refers to Muḥammad’s practice of doing sujūd when reciting Qurʾān 84:1. Abū Ibrāhīm or Abū ʿUthmān Muḥammad b. Qays al-Madinī al-Zayāt, A mawlā of Yaʿqūb al-Qibṭī, is not mentioned as an informant in the redaction of Ibn Hishām It is interesting to note that Ibn Qays is described here as a “storyteller.” The context of Ibn Qays hearing the tradition was when he was telling stories to ʿUmar b. ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz, when ʿUmar was governor of Madīnah. According to Ibn Qutaybah, ʿUmar b. ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz was appointed governor of Madīnah in the year 86/705 and served for seven years and five months, or until 94/712 (QKMXV01P359B). Muḥammad b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān al-Sakāwī, Ibn Qays died in Madīnah during the fitnah of al-Walīd b. Yazīd (MSTMV02P569B), which occured in 126/743 (this event killed many ḥadīth enthusiasts and prominent Madīnans, see TKHLV01P421H). Abū Salamah b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. ʿAwf b. ʿAbd ʿAwf b. al-Ḥārith is not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishāmin any isnād. According to Ibn Saʿd, he died in 94/712 or 104/722 (TKXXV05P120B) and collected traditions from Abū Hurayrah (see TKXXV04P252A). Placement is in section referring to the prophet's practices in prayer. 

