# @comment: TKXXV04P225A to TKXXV04P226A states ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Awfī was a companion who participated in seven campaigns with the prophet. He was also known as Ibn Abī Awfī. He traveled to Kūfah where he died in 86. He is said to have been present at Ḥudaybīyah (TKXXV06P98A). TKXXV06P98A and MDFXV01P101A identifies Abū Awfā as ʿAlqamah b. Khālid b. al-Ḥārith b. Abī Usayd b. Rifāʿah b. Thaʿlabah b. Hawāzin b. Aslam b. Aqṣā b. Ḥārithah b. ʿAmr b. ʿĀmir al-Aslamī. ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Awfī is not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. A Nuʿmān b. Abī Awfā is mentioned as one of Muḥammad's Jewish adversaries among the Banū Qaynuqāʿ, see HSNXV01P514A. ʿAlqamah b. Khālid is not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. 

