PageV34P174
# @ COMMENT: This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. Placement based on content. ʿAbd Allāh b. Mughaffal was one of the weepers before the Battle of Mūʾtah who were given camels in order to participate in the battle. The reference to camels here might refer to the Battle of Mūʾtah but without more evidence I am unable to place it. 

