# @COMMENT: This passage is not found in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. This is an attribution fragment for ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. ʿAmmār b. Abī Zaynab. His full name was ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. ʿAmmār b. Abī Zaynab al-Taymī al-Madinī. He is recorded as transmitting from just two people: al-Qāsim b. Muḥammad b. Abī Bakr al-Ṣiddīq and Abū Bakr b. Muḥammad b. ʿAmr b. Ḥazm. Besides Ibn Isḥāq, he also related stories to Yaḥyā b. Saʿīd al-Qaṭṭān and Yazīd b. ʿAbd al-Allāh b. al-Hād (MZTXV17P295B). No date of death is found. He is not mentioned as a source or a character in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. There does not appear to be any extant traditions that Ibn Isḥāq related from ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. ʿAmmār and he is not otherwise mentioned in the corpus. Placement in the ṭabaqāt section. @EC_03/02/23@

