# @BKHBV01P327A_BEG_WSACD قال لي زهير بن حرب حدثنا يعقوب حدثنا أبي عن ابن إسحاق قال حدثني إبراهيم بن موسى عن عكرمة بن خالد عن الحارث بن عبد الله بن أبي ربيعة عن أبيه صلى بنا عمر بن الخطاب الغداة بالمزدلفة ثم أهل @BKHBV01P327A_END_WSACD
PageV01P327
# @COMMENT: BKHBV01P327A is placed in the biography of the transmitter of the passage, Ibrāhīm b. Mūsā b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān. No other context is given. Ibrāhīm b. Mūsā is not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Rabīʿah b. al-Mughīrah al-Makhzūmī is mentioned by Ibn Isḥāq in the redaction of Ibn Hishām as being one of the two Qurashīs sent to Abyssinia for retrieve migrants (HSNXV01P333A to vol. 1, 337A, and also in the witness of WSACD see HBFXV01P278A, HBHXV03P263A, NYHXV01P115A, and HBHXV37P170A). He is also described as being one of the instigators of the Battle of Uḥud (HSNXV02P060A, for the witness of bn Saʿd see DHRQV01P353A). ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Rabīʿah is cited as a witness to ʿUmar in several traditions (see MDRXV04P2044A, KTMXV03P855A, DKHXV05P474A in a passage from Ibn Isḥāq witnessed by WYSAU). He was appointed govenor of Yemen by ʿUmar and remaioned in that position after the rise of ʿUthmān, for whom he advocated during the majlis following ʿUmar's murder (TBRCV01P2785A). According to BKHBV05P009A he died during the siege of ʿUthmān's home when, in the rush to assist him, ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Rabīʿah fell from his camel and died. Note: BKHBV01P327A might belong in the attributes of ʿUmar section, that often follows an important person's death. Will leave in biography section unless more evidence arrises that supports placement elsewhere. BKHBV01P327A refers to the moring prayer at al-Muzdalifah on the morning of the third day of the pilgrimage. According to Ibn Isḥāq, ʿUmar led the pilgrimage for the first time in 12/634 (see TBRCV01P2078A). Quoting Ibn ʿUmar, al-Ṭabarī also states that ʿUmar led the pilgrimage every year of his caliphate except to the first (TBRCV01P2212B). BKHBV01P296A quotes Ibn Isḥāq as transmitting another tradition from Ibrāhīm b. Mūsā b. ʿAbd al-Raḥmān but does not provide a witness. Ibn Isḥāq is quoted as saying: وقد روى ابن إسحاق سمع ابراهيم بن موسى ابن عبد الرحمن بن عبد الله بن أبي ربيعة عن عكرمة بن خالد ومات عبد الله بن أبي ربيعة قبل عثمان بقليل وكانت أم كلثوم تحت طلحة فكأن عبد الرحمن تزوجها. It appears, therefore that Ibrāhīm b. Mūsā was a source of biographical material. Based on Shamela search (9/15/22) these are the only references to any tradition related by Ibrāhīm b. Mūsā to Ibn Isḥāq. This appears to be the only reference to the passage in the corpus. According to MISMV01P377A, ʿAbd Allāh b. Abī Rabīʿah had married a woman whom ʿUmar later married. ʿUmar divorced her before consummating the marriage. 

