# @ZTKXV01P500A_BEG_WSACD وهو فضالة من عبيد بن نافذ حدثنا بذاك أبي عن @TR2_YISI@ يعقوب بن إبراهيم عن @TR1_SACD@ أبيه عن ابن إسحاق عن يزيد بن أبي حبيب عن أبي مرزوق مولى تجيب عن حنش الصنعاني @ZTKXV01P500A_END_WSACD
PageV01P500
# @COMMENT: ZTKXV01P500A quotes Ibn Isḥāq to highlight a dispute over the indenty of Fadalah. Some assert he is Fadalah b. ʿUbayd b. Nafīdh but Ibn Isḥāq is quoted as stating, via WSACD, that he is Fadalah from the ʿUbayd b. Nafīdh clan. According to DRQMV02P694A, in a non-Ibn Isḥāq tradition, Hanash al-Sanʿānī is quoted as saying that he and Fadalah participated together in a battle in which he and his companions were awarded a necklace (كنا مع فضالة بن عبيد في غزوة فطارت لي ولأصحابي قلادة) in a statement analogous to MDMXV01P645A found above in the story of the Battle of Khaybar. This scene is not mentioned in the redaction of Ibn Hishām. Fadalah b. ʿUbayd is mentioned in Ibn Isḥāq traditions via the witness of WYUAU in SHBMV03P028A, THSHV08P320A, STBXV18P316A, KTHJV07P020A; the witness of WMUTK in HBHXV39P359A, TDSHV12P037A, AAIMV02P066A; the witness of WHSDB THSHV01P330A, THSHV02P096A, TDSHV12P036A, STBXV18P316A, MZSHV08P263A, KTHJV07P020A, AAIMV02P066A, RZIXV03P063A; the witness of WAKMW in STBXV18P313A, BQSXV03P576A; and unwitnessed traditions in IBTTV04P081A, TDSHV62P111A.

